{{infobox Chinese|l=Yin Water Ox|kanji=癸丑|romaji=mizunoto ushi|onyomi=kichū|p=guǐchǒu|w=kuei-ch'ou|mi=kʷeɪ̯²¹ ʈʂʰoʊ̯|y=gwai2 chau2|j=gwai2 chau2|ci=kʷɐi tsʰɐu̯|mc=kjwɨj tʂʰjuw|oc-bs=kʷeʔ ʈʂʰuʔ}} {{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}} '''Yin Water Ox also known as Kinoe-Ushi''' (癸丑, みずのとうし, きすいのうし, きちゅう) is one of the combinations in the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|Sexagenary cycle comprehensive|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
It is the 50th combination in the cycle, following {{ill|Mizunoe-Ne|ja|壬子|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and preceding {{ill|Kō-Inu|ja|甲寅|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. According to {{ill|Yin-Yang and Five Elements|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}癸 represents Yin Water, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}丑 represents Yin Earth, creating a {{ill|Conquest in Five Elements|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|lt=relationship of conquest|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (Earth conquers Water).
