It is the 50th combination in the cycle, following {{ill|Mizunoe-Ne|ja|壬子|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and preceding {{ill|Kō-Inu|ja|甲寅|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. According to {{ill|Yin-Yang and Five Elements|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}癸 represents Yin Water, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}丑 represents Yin Earth, creating a {{ill|Conquest in Five Elements|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|lt=relationship of conquest|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (Earth conquers Water).
