{{infobox Chinese|l=Yin Water Ox|kanji=癸丑|romaji=mizunoto ushi|onyomi=kichū|p=guǐchǒu|w=kuei-ch'ou|mi=kʷeɪ̯²¹ ʈʂʰoʊ̯|y=gwai2 chau2|j=gwai2 chau2|ci=kʷɐi tsʰɐu̯|mc=kjwɨj tʂʰjuw|oc-bs=kʷeʔ ʈʂʰuʔ|qq=}} {{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive|qq=}} '''Yin Water Ox also known as Kinoe-Ushi''' (癸丑, みずのとうし, きすいのうし, きちゅう) is one of the combinations in the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|Sexagenary cycle comprehensive|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sexagenary cycle|qq=}}.
It is the 50th combination in the cycle, following {{ill|Mizunoe-Ne|ja|1=Yang Water Rat|2=ja|壬子|1=Yang Water Rat|2=ja|3=壬子|4=zh|5=壬子|6=ko|7=임자|lt_ko=임자|8=fr|9=Rat de eau|10=de|11=Wasser-Ratte|12=en|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yang Water Rat|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mizunoe-Ne|qq=}} and preceding {{ill|Kō-Inu|ja|1=Yang Wood Tiger|2=ja|甲寅|1=Yang Wood Tiger|2=ja|3=甲寅|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kō-Inu|13=User:Immanuelle/Yang Wood Tiger|qq=}}. According to {{ill|Yin-Yang and Five Elements|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang and Five Elements|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Heavenly Stems|qq=}}癸 represents Yin Water, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Earthly Branches|qq=}}丑 represents Yin Earth, creating a {{ill|Conquest in Five Elements|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|lt=relationship of conquest|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Conquest in Five Elements|qq=}} (Earth conquers Water).
