It is the 50th combination in the cycle, following {{ill|Mizunoe-Ne|ja|1=Yang Water Rat|2=ja|壬子|1=Yang Water Rat|2=ja|3=壬子|4=zh|5=壬子|6=ko|7=임자|lt_ko=임자|8=fr|9=Rat de eau|10=de|11=Wasser-Ratte|12=en|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yang Water Rat|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mizunoe-Ne|qq=}} and preceding {{ill|Kō-Inu|ja|1=Yang Wood Tiger|2=ja|甲寅|1=Yang Wood Tiger|2=ja|3=甲寅|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kō-Inu|13=User:Immanuelle/Yang Wood Tiger|qq=}}. According to {{ill|Yin-Yang and Five Elements|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang and Five Elements|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=}}, the [[:en:Heavenly Stems|Heavenly Stems]]癸 represents Yin Water, while the [[:en:Earthly Branches|Earthly Branches]]丑 represents Yin Earth, creating a {{ill|Conquest in Five Elements|ja|五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|lt=relationship of conquest|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Conquest in Five Elements|qq=}} (Earth conquers Water).
==Pronunciation== PronounciationYin Water Ox \n<!-- == * Yin Water Ox (癸丑) ** Chinese (Mandarin Pinyin): guǐchǒu ** Cantonese (Jyutping): gwai2 cau2 ** Japanese: ***Kunyomi: みずのとうし (mizunoto-ushi) ***Onyomi: きかのうし (kika-no-ushi) ***Onyomi: きちゅう (kichū) ** Korean (Revised Romanization): gyechuk ** Vietnamese (Hán-Việt): Quý Sửu
--> ==Years of Yin Water Ox== Gregorian calendar years that leave a remainder of 53 when divided by 60 correspond to years of Kinoe-Ushi.
{| class="wikitable" |+ '''Years of Kinoe-Ushi''' |- ! [[1st Millennium]] !! [[2nd Millennium]] !! [[3rd Millennium]] |- | * [[53]] * [[113]] * [[173]] * [[233]] * [[293]] * [[353]] * [[413]] * [[473]] * [[533]] * [[593]] * [[653]] * [[713]] * [[773]] * [[833]] * [[893]] * [[953]] | * [[1013]] * [[1073]] * [[1133]] * [[1193]] * [[1253]] * [[1313]] * [[1373]] * [[1433]] * [[1493]] * [[1553]] * [[1613]] * [[1673]] * [[1733]] * [[1793]] * [[1853]] * [[1913]] * [[1973]] | * [[2033]] * [[2093]] * [[2153]] * [[2213]] * [[2273]] * [[2333]] * [[2393]] * [[2453]] * [[2513]] * [[2573]] * [[2633]] * [[2693]] * [[2753]] * [[2813]] * [[2873]] * [[2933]] * [[2993]] |}
==Months of Yin Water Ox== The twelfth month (December) of Gregorian calendar years ending in 2 or 7 (Heavenly Stems 壬 or 丁) corresponds to Kinoe-Ushi months. However, this applies to the {{ill|Lunar calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lunar calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} or [[:en:Solar term|Solar terms]] (from [[:en:Xiaohan|Shōkan]] to the day before [[:en:Lichun|Risshun]]) in traditional contexts.
==Days of Yin Water Ox== === Auspicious Dates === Days of Kinoe-Ushi are noted as intercalary days during the {{ill|Hassen|ja|八専|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hassen|qq=}} period. == See Also == * {{prefix|qq=}} * {{intitle|qq=}}
